title: Memory voltage adjustment
textBeforeTable: memory voltage select GPIO5 bit0 memory voltage select GPIO5 bit5 bit5 and bit0 are outputs, rest is input. no inversions. GPIO5 (0xE1) input GPIO2 bit 0 input GPIO2 bit 1 output always 1 ??? GPIO2 bit 2 0 = VID can be changed 1 = LockVID GPIO2 bit 3 1 = 1.5V Chipset voltage 0 = 1.6V Chipset voltage GPIO2 bit 4 1 = vcore offset + 100mV 0 = vcore offset + 200mV GPIO2 bit 5 memory voltage select GPIO2 bit 6 memory voltage select GPIO2 bit7 No inversions, bit0 and bit1 inputs, rest configured as outputs. GPIO2 (0xE4) It seems only GPIO2 and GPIO5 is used from W83627EHF/EHG.
